earn_20260429_075816.log\n60\t\n61\t---\n62\t## Session 2 -- 2026-04-29 07:58\n63\t\n64\tAdded two generalization strategies in `agent/active_operators.py`:\n65\t\n66\t- **`rect_interior_fill`** -- detects hollow rectangular borders of a single\n67\t  foreground color on a background, learns a map\n68\t  `(interior_h, interior_w) -> fill_color` from training pairs, and fills\n69\t  matching rectangle interiors in the test input. Solves c0f76784.\n70\t- **`staircase_extend_right`** -- detects 1-row inputs that produce\n71\t  triangular outputs of `w//2` rows where each row's colored prefix grows\n72\t  by one cell. Identifies fg as the leftmost cell and bg as the only\n73\t  other color (avoids a \"most common color = bg\" trap when fg fills most\n74\t  of the row). Solves bbc9ae5d.\n75\t\n76\tVerification:\n77\t- `python run_task.py` (regression on 08ed6ac7): CORRECT\n78\t- `python run_learn.py --limit 20 --shuffle`: 4 / 20 (20.0%), up from 2 / 20\n79\t  - c0f76784: CORRECT via rect_interior_fill (pipeline)\n80\t  - bbc9ae5d: CORRECT via staircase_extend_right (pipeline)\n81\t  - 8be77c9e, c59eb873: CORRECT via stored rules\n82\t- Rules: 5 -> 7 (+2 new strategies stored in procedural_memory/)\n83\t\n84\t---\n85\t## Learning Loop -- 2026-04-29 07:59\n86\t\n87\t- Split: None, Tasks: 20\n88\t- Correct: 4 / 20 (20.0%)\n89\t- Rules: 7 -> 7 (+0 learned)\n90\t- Stored rule hits: 4\n91\t- Time: 8s\n92\t- Log: logs/learn_20260429_075851.log\n93\t\n94\t---\n95\t## Learning Loop -- 2026-04-29 08:07\n96\t\n97\t- Split: None, Tasks: 20\n98\t- Correct: 6 / 20 (30.0%)\n99\t- Rules: 10 -> 10 (+0 learned)\n100\t- Stored rule hits: 6\n101\t- Time: 9s\n102\t- Log: logs/learn_20260429_080656.log\n103\t\n104\t---\n105\t## Session 3 -- 2026-04-29 08:07\n106\t\n107\tAdded two generalization strategies in `agent/active_operators.py`:\n108\t\n109\t- **`corner_quadrant_fill`** -- detects N solid rectangles of one shared\n110\t  \"inner color\" each surrounded by 4 single-cell corner markers 